Amgen Inc. is a leading biotechnology company with a strong presence in the autoimmune disease space. The company has been actively working on developing biologic therapies for autoimmune hemolytic anemia, aiming to provide targeted and effective treatments for patients. Pfizer Inc., a renowned pharmaceutical company, is also involved in the development of treatments for autoimmune disorders, including autoimmune hemolytic anemia. Their innovative approaches to therapy development hold promise for improving patient outcomes in this challenging disease.

